  <span id="freeText4477031316789838297" style="display:none">i am not going to review this beyond saying that this is an absolute must read book. for everyone.<br /><br />---------------<br /><br />as i finish up my month of reading Black authors, this one's for all my white people out there: if you think the solution to ending racism is reading a certain book or combination of books, you have a lot more work to do! this is only the start.<br /><br />---<br /><br /><i>i am spending this month reading books by Black authors. please join me!</i><br /><br />book 1: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2953004100?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Stars and the Blackness Between Them</a><br />book 2: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372388250?type=review#rating_290994509" rel="nofollow noopener">Homegoing</a><br />book 3: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2718387154?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Let's Talk about Love</a><br />book 4: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3090142486?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Why I'm No Longer Talking to White People about Race</a><br />book 5: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3227618881?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Sellout</a><br />book 6: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372395187?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Queenie</a><br />book 7: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372400231?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Red at the Bone</a><br />book 8: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2586355320?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Weight of the Stars</a><br />book 9: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372396230?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">An American Marriage</a><br />book 10: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372415062?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Dea